    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <head>No. 346.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">Edward
                                    Thornton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-12-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 17,
                                    1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 23d ultimo, with its several inclosures, in
                            relation to an attack alleged to have been made by a number of Gros
                            Ventres and Mandin Indians from the United States upon a party of Stony
                            Indians of Canada, during which about eight of the latter were killed
                            and several more wounded.</p>
                <p>In reply I beg to inform you that I have communicated a copy of your note
                            to my colleague, the Secretary of the Interior, in order that the facts
                            may be inquired into, with a view to such action by this government as
                            may be found to be proper.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
